<subSubSection id="C30FB290352AFFE6FF17FA6FFF7BF997" pageId="9" pageNumber="365" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B352AFFE6FF17FA6FFF7BF997" blockId="9.[151,1437,1437,2040]" pageId="9" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis id="B9613D09352AFFE6FF17FA6FFEA5FA4B" bold="true" box="[151,266,1437,1463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="365">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The placement of the embolus (e), tegular apophysis (Ta) and median apophysis toward the distal tip of the palp is more extreme in 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A98352AFFE6FE4DFA30FD8AFA27" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[461,549,1473,1499]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lorax">
<emphasis id="B9613D09352AFFE6FE4DFA30FD8AFA27" box="[461,549,1473,1499]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="365">L. lorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that in other 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A98352AFFE6FD39FA30FCC7FA27" box="[697,872,1473,1499]" pageId="9" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis id="B9613D09352AFFE6FD39FA30FCBFFA27" box="[697,784,1474,1499]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="365">Lapsias</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(Maddison 2006). Males recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F302A18B352AFFE6FAAEFA33FA33FA27" box="[1326,1436,1473,1499]" name="Colombia" pageId="9" pageNumber="365">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49D12FF9352AFFE6FF1FFA17FF51F9FC" box="[159,254,1509,1536]" country="Colombia" name="Quindio" pageId="9" pageNumber="365">Quindio</collectingRegion>
) do not present the yellow bars across the chelicerae. Females can be recognized by the semirounded spermathecae (sp) placed posteriorly, the short and lateral copulatory ducts (cd), the anterior copulatory openings (co), and the long overhanging projection that arise in the anterior edge of the epigynal plate and exceed the posterior edge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
